main.formObjects

Class FitnessTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.formObjects.FitnessTest

  • public class FitnessTest
extends java.lang.Object
    FitnessTest object. This fitness test object is used to hold the information that is contained inside of the Fitness Testing Data Sheet tab.

    Holds getters/setters for all variables, as well as methods for converting the profile to HTML and a pdf, as well as methods for interacting with the database

      • addRow

        public void addRow(boolean viewInfo,
                   java.lang.String DBindex)
        Adds a row to the database class. It is used in conjunction with the other forms, since the value for each table is autoincremented.
        Parameters:
        viewInfo - Boolean value for if you should insert the data into the database (false), or if you should update the athlete in the database (true)
        DBindex - Index of the athlete in the database. The Athlete's ID. Used when updating the athlete in teh database (when the viewInfo param holds value of true)
